What are some of the defining features that set apart animals adapted to nocturnal behavior from their diurnal counterparts? Also, can you provide a brief explanation of what is meant by "nocturnal animals"? 
[Swift code]: 
Here is some Swift code that simulates animal behavior based on whether they are nocturnal or diurnal:
class Animal {
    var isNocturnal: Bool

    init(nocturnal: Bool) {
        self.isNocturnal = nocturnal
    }

    func sleep() {
        if isNocturnal {
            print("Sleeping during the day")
        } else {
            print("Sleeping at night")
        }
    }

    func hunt() {
        if isNocturnal {
            print("Hunting at night")
        } else {
            print("Hunting during the day")
        }
    }
}
let owl = Animal(nocturnal: true)
let lion = Animal(nocturnal: false)
owl.hunt() // Output: Hunting at night
lion.sleep() // Output: Sleeping at night
Can you see how the behavior of these animals changes based on whether they are nocturnal or diurnal?
